The paper deals with the problem of mining cohesive subgraphs in bipartite graphs, which is a common topic in data mining and graph theory. The proposed algorithms and techniques involve data structures, indexing, and optimization, which are typical areas of research in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
